1. Open up the terminal, be in the root directory
2. Run this command "npm init"
3. Press Enter until a node project is initiated
4. Install the following dependencies
  * express - A node framework
  * nodemon - Node package to rerun the node server after every changes made
  * bcryptjs - Used to hash or hide password
  * mongoose - Used to connect to MongoDB database
  * cors - Cross Origin Resource Sharing
 Run "npm install express nodemon bcryptjs mongoose cors"
5. Add a "start" script in your package.json with "nodemon backend/server".js".



====== HTTP Requests ======
get - Read Data
post - Create Data
put - Update Data
delete - Destroy Data

CRUD Operation 
C - Create
R - Read
U - Update
D - Destroy